      "stem": "An 18-month-old child, who recently immigrated to the country, presents with increased work of breathing. Physical examination is significant for perioral cyanosis, tachypnea, a single loud S2, and a 3/6 systolic ejection murmur heard best at the lower left sternal border. ECG shows right axis deviation and right ventricular hypertrophy. Chest radiograph obtained is shown in Figure 10.2. What is the MOST LIKELY diagnosis?",
